                           <div class="detaildropdown-content">
                                                                                          <div class="detailfaq-item">
                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>1. Where is the Brahmatal Trek located?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    Brahmatal Trek is located in the Chamoli district of Uttarakhand, India, near Lohajung village in the Garhwal Himalayas.                                 </div>
                              </div>
                                                            <div class="detailfaq-item">
                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>2. What is the altitude of Brahmatal?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    The trek reaches a maximum altitude of around 12,250 ft (3734 m).                                 </div>
                              </div>
                                                            <div class="detailfaq-item">
                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>3. How many days does the trek take?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    The trek itinerary is 5 nights – 6 days, from Dehradun to Dehradun or Rishikesh.                                 </div>
                              </div>
                                                            <div class="detailfaq-item">
                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>4. Is Brahmatal a good trek for beginners?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    Yes, it’s considered Easy to Moderate in difficulty — suitable for beginners with average fitness.                                 </div>
                              </div>
                                                            <div class="detailfaq-item">
                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>5. Why is the Brahmatal Trek famous?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    It’s known for snow trekking, beautiful alpine lakes, and panoramic views of Mt. Trishul and Mt. Nanda Ghunti.                                 </div>
                              </div>
                                                            <div class="detailfaq-item">
                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>6. When is the best time to do the Brahmatal Trek?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    <p><span style="font-weight: bold;">Winter: </span>December to February (for snow);&nbsp;</p>
<p><span style="font-weight: bold;">Spring: </span>March to April (for clear skies and rhododendron blooms).</p>                                 </div>
                              </div>
                                                            <div class="detailfaq-item">
                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>7. Can the trek be done in monsoon?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    No, the monsoon season (July–August) is not suitable due to heavy rainfall and slippery trails.                                 </div>
                              </div>
                                                            <div class="detailfaq-item">
                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>8. Will I get to see snow?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    Yes, December to February offers the best chance to trek on snow-covered trails.                                 </div>
                              </div>
                                                            <div class="detailfaq-item">
